  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with a comprehensive legal framework designed to prevent, detect, and punish such activities. Here's an overview of the key aspects:\n\n1. International Legal Framework\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) Recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act (AMLA)\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- International anti-money laundering statutes\n\n3. Regulatory Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n- Risk assessment procedures\n\n4. Legal Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n5. Prevention Mechanisms\n- Enhanced financial reporting\n- Cross-border transaction tracking\n- International information sharing\n- Compliance training programs\n\n6. Core Legal Principles\n- Identifying illegal financial flows\n- Tracing criminal proceeds\n- Disrupting financial criminal networks\n- Protecting financial system integrity\n\nThese frameworks aim to comprehensively address money laundering risks across different jurisdictions.",
